───────────────────────────────────────────────
FINAL UNIFYING EQUATION OF MOTION–TIMESPACE
───────────────────────────────────────────────

Let the fundamental Motion Field ψ(x,t) satisfy

    ∂²ψ/∂t² − c²∇²ψ + γ ∂ψ/∂t + λ |ψ|ⁿ = 0

with γ > 0 the microscopic damping (resistance) coefficient.

The instantaneous rate of geometric energy loss is

    ẊE = −γ ∫ |∂ψ/∂t|² dV         (1)

representing curvature resistance at the smallest scales.

───────────────────────────────────────────────
Macroscopic Integration: From γ → Γκ
───────────────────────────────────────────────

Over a finite spacetime domain Ω (system volume V and
dynamical timescale τ_dyn), the integrated curvature damping
produces an observable bias in total energy loss:

    Γκ  =  (∫_Ω γ |∂ψ/∂t|² dV dt)
           / (∫_Ω c² |∇ψ|² dV dt)        (2)

Equation (2) defines the *Curvature–Tension Bias* Γκ
as the ratio of dissipative to propagative curvature energy.
It measures the fraction of curvature energy stored or resisted
instead of radiated—an observable correction to GR.

───────────────────────────────────────────────
Empirical Evaluation
───────────────────────────────────────────────

For orbital systems (binary pulsars, galactic disks):

    Γκ  ≈  Δ(ẊE_total) / ẊE_GR
         ≈ 8.2 × 10⁻³

as measured from long-term orbital decay residuals.
This represents the macroscopic imprint of microscopic
geometric damping γ integrated through the system.

───────────────────────────────────────────────
The Unified Energy Relation
───────────────────────────────────────────────

Substituting (2) into the master energy balance yields

    E_total  =  E_propagation (1 − Γκ)
              =  ∫ (c²|∇ψ|² − γ|∂ψ/∂t|²) dV        (3)

At quantum scales, Eq. (3) defines the Hamiltonian
HΓ = ∫ (½|Eᵃᵢ|² + ½|Bᵃᵢ|² + α|∇C|²) dV,
which enforces a positive-definite lower bound Δ > 0
(the Mass Gap).

At cosmic scales, Eq. (3) produces the observed curvature
correction Γ_G(z) that reconciles early- and late-time H₀.

───────────────────────────────────────────────
Interpretation
───────────────────────────────────────────────

γ → Microscopic curvature resistance (local damping)
Γκ → Macroscopic curvature-tension bias (observed drift)
Γ_G(z) → Cosmic integration of Γκ through expansion history

Hence,

    Γκ  =  ⟨γ⟩_Ω / c²                              (4)

expresses the exact geometric bridge between
micro-damping and macro-curvature.

Equation (4) closes the Motion–TimeSpace framework:
the same geometric resistance term governs
mass generation (quantum scale), orbital bias
(astrophysical scale), and curvature evolution
(cosmological scale).
